Φ(Ontology Flesh) = σ(seer|seen) ∘ ρ(body|world) ∘ λ(abstract|embodied) ∘ β(perception|expression) ∘ δγ(visible|invisible) ∘ μ(chiasm|reversibility) + ε | :intercorporeal_unity

## Operator Breakdown

- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: seer|seen — Distinguished only to reveal their reversibility in the chiasm; touching and being touched are one event.
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: body|world — Perception is active embodied engagement, not passive reception; body and world reciprocally enfold.
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: abstract|embodied — Transforms abstract philosophy into embodied phenomenology prioritizing lived experience.
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: perception|expression — Expression reveals new ways of seeing; art and language are generative acts.
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: visible|invisible — Perceptual experience cycles between what shows itself and what withdraws.
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: chiasm|reversibility — The architectural principle of flesh: subject and object in reciprocal exchange.

## Z-State
:intercorporeal_unity — Perceiving subject and perceived object share a common flesh.

